Description: Sherd of shoulder and turn of neck of pottery closed vase, probably an amphora; near fine grey-brown clay with dull cream slip. Incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 649)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JA.097)
